# Custom field mapping

Custom field mapping lets your integration declare a set of custom fields that should exist on candidates (or jobs) in Teamtailor. When the user activates your integration, they can either map each of your fields to a custom field they already have, or let Teamtailor **create the custom field for them** automatically.

Once a field is mapped, the candidate's (or job's) value for that field is included in the [webhook](#webhooks) payload we send you — keyed by the `apiName` you chose, so you always receive the data under names you control, regardless of how the field is named inside the customer's Teamtailor account.

Use this when your integration needs to read structured data the recruiter maintains in Teamtailor (for example a "Seniority", "Preferred language" or "Notice period" field) without asking every customer to set fields up by hand.

## How it works

1. You declare the fields you care about in a `customFieldMapping` array, as part of your [activation config](#webhook-activation-config).
2. During activation, the user sees your declared fields and, for each one, chooses to **map it to an existing custom field** or **create a new field** with the name and type you specified.
3. If they choose to create, Teamtailor creates the custom field on the account. Fields are created only once — activating again will not create duplicates.
4. From then on, whenever we send a webhook for that candidate or job, the values of the mapped fields are included in the `custom-fields` array, keyed by your `apiName`.

## Declaring the mapping

```json
{
  "config": {
    "fields": [
      {
        "id": "clientId",
        "type": "text",
        "label": "Client ID",
        "required": true
      }
    ],
    "customFieldMapping": [
      {
        "name": "Preferred language",
        "type": "select",
        "apiName": "preferred-language",
        "options": ["English", "French", "German"]
      },
      {
        "name": "Years of experience",
        "type": "number",
        "apiName": "years-of-experience"
      },
      {
        "name": "Available from",
        "type": "date",
        "apiName": "available-from"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Add a `customFieldMapping` array next to `fields` inside your activation config. You can provide this config in either of the ways described in the [Webhook activation config](#webhook-activation-config) section:

- as a **static config** set on the [Partner resource](#partners) (recommended when the fields are the same for every customer), or
- returned by your **dynamic activation endpoint** (`GET ${BASE_URL}/activation`) when you need to build the list per customer.

### Custom field mapping objects

Attribute | Type   | Required | Description
----------|--------|----------|------------
name      | string | Yes      | Human readable name. Used as the field's name in Teamtailor when a new field is created.
type      | string | Yes      | The custom field type (see below).
apiName   | string | Yes      | The identifier you want this field to be sent under in the webhook payload. It is normalized to lowercase kebab-case (for example `Years Of Experience` becomes `years-of-experience`), so prefer providing it in that form.
options   | array  | Conditional | List of option values. **Required** for `select` and `multiselect` — fields of these types are skipped if no options are supplied.

### Supported types

Type          | Description
--------------|------------
text          | Free text
number        | Numeric value
date          | Date
checkbox      | Boolean (true / false)
select        | Single choice from `options`
multiselect   | Multiple choices from `options`
url           | URL
phone         | Phone number

Unknown types are ignored.

## Receiving mapped values in webhooks

Mapped fields are delivered in the candidate's (and, where relevant, the job's) `custom-fields` array in the [webhook payload](#webhooks). Each entry is keyed by your `apiName` and contains the field `value`, its `type`, and `mapped-from` — the original field name as it exists in the customer's Teamtailor account.

```json
{
  "custom-fields": [
    {
      "preferred-language": {
        "value": ["English"],
        "type": "select",
        "mapped-from": "spoken-language"
      }
    },
    {
      "years-of-experience": {
        "value": 8,
        "type": "number",
        "mapped-from": "experience-years"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Attribute   | Description
------------|------------
value       | The candidate's or job's value for the field. For `select`/`multiselect` this is a list of selected option values; for `number` it is numeric; for `checkbox` it is a boolean.
type        | The field type as stored in Teamtailor: `text`, `number`, `date`, `boolean`, `select`, `multiselect`, `url`, `phone`, `email`.
mapped-from | The field's actual `apiName` inside the customer's account. Present only when the field was mapped through custom field mapping.

A field appears in the payload only when the candidate (or job) has a value for it. If the recruiter has not filled in the field, it is omitted.
